<%- include('../partials/header') %>

    <section class="product-banner py-5">
        <img src="images/EQ9.png" alt="product image" class="banner-bg-img">
        <div class="container">

            <div class="text-content-banner">
                <div class="breadcrumb">
                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
                        <a href="/">Home</a>
                        <span class="mx-2" style="font-weight: 400; color: #999;">&gt;</span>

                        <a href="/products/<%= categorySlug %>">
                            <%= categoryName %>
                        </a>
                        <span class="mx-2" style="font-weight: 400; color: #999;">&gt;</span>

                        <strong>
                            <%= brandName %>
                        </strong>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h1>
                    <%= brandName %>
                </h1>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


    <section class="product-content">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="text-lg-start">

                <!-- When MCB Tab is open then show this content -->
                <div class="for-MCB">
<h2 class="fw-bolder">

    EQ9 Miniature Circuit Breakers (MCBs) <br class="d-lg-block d-none"> from 0.5A To 63 A

</h2>
<p>
    Alric Electric’s EQ9 series premium MCBs provides reliable and safe protection against overloads and
    short circuits with
    best-in-class technology <br class="d-lg-block d-none"> and infrastructure. These MCBs are
    manufactured with recyclable
    fire-retardant engineering
    plastics ensuring safety and durability. <br class="d-lg-block d-none">
    These MCBs are must-have safety product for distribution of power at homes, residential / commercial
    buildings /
    industrial applications.  
</p>
                </div>
                <!-- When Isolator  Tab is open then show this content -->
                <div class="for-Isolator">
<h2 class="fw-bolder">

EQ9 Miniature Circuit Breakers (MCBs) from 0.5A to 63A

</h2>
<p>
Alric Electric’s EQ9 series premium MCBs provides reliable and safe protection against overloads and short circuits with
best-in-class technology  <br  class="d-lg-block d-none" > and infrastructure. These MCBs are manufactured with recyclable fire-retardant engineering
plastics ensuring safety and durability. <br class="d-lg-block d-none">
These MCBs are must-have safety product for distribution of power at homes, residential / commercial buildings /
industrial applications.  
</p>
                </div>
                <!-- When Auralis  Tab is open then show this content -->
              
                <div class="for-Auralis">
<h2 class="fw-bolder">
Auralis DBs

</h2>
<p>
This range is crafted for demanding installations, offering high‑precision protection, advanced safety features, and
premium‑grade materials. <br class="d-lg-block d-none" >
Auralic DBs offers perfect solution for high‑end residential and commercial projects, corporate environments,
architect‑specified installations, builders and industry. 
</p>

<!-- On Click THis button Show below ul list -->
<span class="show-list" > Read More <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i> </span>

<ul class="show-list" >
    <li>
        Aesthetically pleasing contemporary DB design with rounded corners of metallic door
    </li>
    <li>
        4-piece architecture DBs consisting of Wall box, DB frame, separate protection shield and DB door, comes with IP43 &
        IK09 protection
    </li>
    <li>
        Can opt for requirements such as IP54 protection, acrylic door, Mivan compatible DBs in 1.6mm thickness or special
        customized Engineered To Order (ETO) DBs
    </li>
    <li>
        DBs supplied with specially developed process by using rust resistant Galvanized Iron (GI) sheet pre-treated with water
        spray-based nano-coating technology
        followed by powder coating. Giving excellent best in class rust protection
    </li>
    <li>
        DB Door can be assembled reversibly on either side of DB providing flexibility to customer at site based on space
        availability.
    </li>
    <li>
        Innovatively designed new Doorknob provides excellent IP protection, is easy to operate with long life and is provided
        with label holder for easy identification of DB.
    </li>
    <li>
        All hardware plated with special Zinc + Nickel alloy providing very high rust resistance matching improved rust
        resistance of DB
    </li>
    <li>
        100A rated Silver plated copper Bus bars instead of used Tin-plated bus bars.
    </li>
</ul>

                </div>



                <!-- When Elvo  Tab is open then show this content -->
              
                <div class="for-elvo">
<h2 class="fw-bolder">
Elvo DBs

</h2>
<p>
This range strikes the perfect balance between performance and affordability. A trusted choice for contractors seeking
long lasting, easy to install solutions.
</p>

<!-- On Click THis button Show below ul list -->
<span class="show-list" > Read More <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i> </span>

<ul class="show-list" >
    <li>
    3-piece architecture DBs consisting of Wall box, DB frame integrated with protection shield and DB door, comes with IP42
    & IK08 protection
    </li>
 
   <li>
    Combines enhanced build quality with modern styling to meet the needs of both residential and commercial users.
   </li>
   <li>
    Offering improved durability, optimised cable space, and better installation convenience
   </li>
   <li>
    DBs supplied with specially developed process by using CRCA steel sheet pre-treated with water spray-based nano-coating
    technology followed by powder coating. Giving robust rust protection
   </li>
   <li>
    DB Door can be assembled reversibly on either side of DB providing flexibility to customer at site based on space
    availability.
   </li>
   <li>
    Innovatively designed new Doorknob provides very good protection, easy to operate with long life
   </li>
   <li>
    All hardware plated with special Zinc + Nickel alloy providing very high rust resistance matching improved rust
    resistance of DB
   </li>
   <li>
    100A rated Silver plated copper Bus bars instead of used Tin-plated bus bars.
   </li>
</ul>

                </div>

                <!-- When Avina  Tab is open then show this content -->
              
                <div class="for-avina">
<h2 class="fw-bolder">
Avina DBs

</h2>
<p>
Avina range Distribution Boards are offered in single & double row SPN & TPN configuration and are designed to deliver
dependable performance for standard residential and light‑commercial electrical installations.
</p>

<!-- On Click THis button Show below ul list -->
<span class="show-list" > Read More <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i> </span>

<ul class="show-list" >
  <li>
    Plastic front facia with CRCA metal back box DBs in SPN / TPN configuration for retail requirements
  </li>
</ul>

                </div>
                

            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="container tab-content active">
            <div class="row">
                <% if(categorySlug==='distribution-boards' ){ %>

                    <div class="product-tabs tabs text-center ">
                        <a href="/products/distribution-boards/auralis?tab=auralis"
                            class="btn <%= activeTab === 'auralis' ? 'btn-theme-danger' : 'btn-theme-danger-outline' %>">
                            Auralis
                        </a>

                        <a href="/products/distribution-boards/elvo?tab=elvo"
                            class="btn <%= activeTab === 'elvo' ?  'btn-theme-danger' : 'btn-theme-danger-outline' %>">
                            Elvo
                        </a>

                        <a href="/products/distribution-boards/avina?tab=avina"
                            class="btn <%= activeTab === 'avina' ?  'btn-theme-danger' : 'btn-theme-danger-outline' %>">
                            Avina
                        </a>


                    </div>

                    <% } %>

                        <% if(brandSlug==='eq9' ){ %>

                            <div class="product-tabs text-center tabs">

                                <a href="?tab=mcb"
                                    class="btn <%= activeTab === 'mcb' ? 'btn-theme-danger' : 'btn-theme-danger-outline' %>">
                                    MCB
                                </a>

                                <a href="?tab=isolator"
                                    class="btn <%= activeTab === 'isolator' ? 'btn-theme-danger' : 'btn-theme-danger-outline' %>">
                                    Isolator
                                </a>

                            </div>

                            <% } %>

                            <div class="row row  justify-content-between">
                                <!-- FILTERS -->
                            
                                <div class="col-lg-3 mb-4">
                            
                                    <div class="filter-box filter ">
                            
                                        <div class="text-lg-start">
                                            <h3>
                                                Filters
                                            </h3>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="dropdown-container">
                                            <form id="filterForm" method="GET">
                            
                                                <input type="hidden" name="tab" value="<%= activeTab %>">
                            
                                                <% if(brandSlug==='eq9' ){ %>
                            
                                                    <!-- Rating -->
                                                    <div class="dropdown-item">
                            
                                                        <input type="checkbox" id="drop1" class="dropdown-check ">
                                                        <label for="drop1" class="dropdown-header">
                                                            <span>current rating</span>
                                                            <span class="dropdown-arrow"></span>
                                                        </label>
                            
                                                        <div class="dropdown-content">
                                                            <% ratings.forEach(function(item){ %>
                            
                                                                <div class="form-check mb-2">
                            
                                                                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" name="rating"
                                                                        value="<%= item %>" <%=Array.isArray(selectedFilters.rating) ?
                                                                        selectedFilters.rating.includes(item) ? 'checked' : '' :
                                                                        selectedFilters.rating===item ? 'checked' : '' %>
                                                                    onchange="document.getElementById('filterForm').submit()">
                            
                            
                                                                    <label class="form-check-label">
                                                                        <%= item %>
                                                                    </label>
                            
                                                                </div>
                            
                                                                <% }) %>
                                                        </div>
                            
                            
                                                    </div>
                            
                                                    <!-- Curve -->
                                                    <div class="dropdown-item">
                                                        <input type="checkbox" id="drop2" class="dropdown-check">
                                                        <label for="drop2" class="dropdown-header">
                                                            <span>curve type</span>
                                                            <span class="dropdown-arrow"></span>
                                                        </label>
                            
                                                        <div class="dropdown-content">
                                                            <% curve_type.forEach(function(item){ %>
                            
                                                                <div class="form-check mb-2">
                            
                                                                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" name="curve_type"
                                                                        value="<%= item %>" <%=Array.isArray(selectedFilters.curve_type) ?
                                                                        selectedFilters.curve_type.includes(item) ? 'checked' : '' :
                                                                        selectedFilters.curve_type===item ? 'checked' : '' %>
                                                                    onchange="document.getElementById('filterForm').submit()">
                            
                            
                                                                    <label class="form-check-label">
                                                                        <%= item %>
                                                                    </label>
                            
                                                                </div>
                            
                                                                <% }) %>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                            
                            
                            
                                                    <!-- Poles -->
                            
                                                    <div class="dropdown-item">
                                                        <input type="checkbox" id="drop3" class="dropdown-check">
                                                        <label for="drop3" class="dropdown-header">
                                                            <span>No Of Poles</span>
                                                            <span class="dropdown-arrow"></span>
                                                        </label>
                                                        <div class="dropdown-content">
                                                            <% poles.forEach(function(item){ %>
                            
                                                                <div class="form-check mb-2">
                            
                                                                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" name="poles" value="<%= item %>"
                                                                        <%=Array.isArray(selectedFilters.poles) ?
                                                                        selectedFilters.poles.includes(item) ? 'checked' : '' :
                                                                        selectedFilters.poles===item ? 'checked' : '' %>
                                                                    onchange="document.getElementById('filterForm').submit()">
                            
                                                                    <label class="form-check-label">
                                                                        <%= item %>
                                                                    </label>
                            
                                                                </div>
                            
                                                                <% }) %>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                            
                            
                            
                                                    <!-- For Boards -->
                            
                                                    <% } %>
                            
                                                        <% boardStructure.forEach(function(group , index){ %>
                            
                                                            <div class="dropdown-item">
                                                                <input type="checkbox" id="drop<%= index %>" class="dropdown-check">
                                                                <label for="drop<%= index %>" class="dropdown-header">
                                                                    <span>
                                                                        <%= group.board %>
                                                                    </span>
                                                                    <span class="dropdown-arrow"></span>
                                                                </label>
                                                                <div class="dropdown-content">
                                                                    <% group.types.forEach(function(type){ %>
                            
                            
                                                                        <div class="form-check">
                            
                                                                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" name="boards_type"
                                                                                value="<%= type %>"
                                                                                onchange="document.getElementById('filterForm').submit()">
                            
                                                                            <label class="form-check-label">
                                                                                <%= type %>
                                                                            </label>
                            
                                                                        </div>
                            
                                                                        <% }) %>
                                                                </div>
                                                            </div>
                            
                            
                            
                                                            <% }) %>
                            
                            
                            
                                            </form>
                            
                                        </div>
                            
                                    </div>
                            
                                </div>
                            
                                <!-- PRODUCT CARDS -->
                            
                                <div class="col-lg-9">
                                    <div class="product-container">
                                        <div class="row align-items-center">
                            
                                            <% products.forEach(function(product){ %>
                            
                                                <div class="col-lg-4 pe-1 mb-4">
                            
                            
                            
                                                    <div class="product-card">
                                                        <a href="/product/<%= product.slug %>">
                                                            <div class="product-card-image">
                            
                                                                <img src="/images/<%= product.image %>" alt="<%= product.name %>" class="img-fluid">
                            
                                                            </div>
                            
                                                            <div class="product-details">
                            
                                                                <h3>
                                                                    <%= product.name %>
                                                                </h3>
                            
                                                            </div>
                                                        </a>
                                                    </div>
                            
                            
                            
                                                </div>
                            
                                                <% }) %>
                                                    <% if(totalPages> 1){ %>
                            
                                                        <div class="row justify-content-center mt-5">
                            
                                                            <div class="col-auto">
                            
                                                                <nav>
                            
                                                                    <ul class="pagination">
                            
                                                                        <% if(page> 1){ %>
                            
                                                                            <li class="page-item">
                                                                                <a class="page-link" href="?page=<%= page - 1 %>">
                                                                                    &lt;
                                                                                </a>
                                                                            </li>
                            
                                                                            <% } %>
                            
                                                                                <% for(let i=1; i <=totalPages; i++){ %>
                            
                                                                                    <li class="page-item <%= page === i ? 'active' : '' %>">
                            
                                                                                        <a class="page-link" href="?page=<%= i %>">
                                                                                            <%= i %>
                                                                                        </a>
                            
                                                                                    </li>
                            
                                                                                    <% } %>
                            
                                                                                        <% if(page < totalPages){ %>
                            
                                                                                            <li class="page-item">
                                                                                                <a class="page-link" href="?page=<%= page + 1 %>">
                                                                                                    &gt;
                                                                                                </a>
                                                                                            </li>
                            
                                                                                            <% } %>
                            
                                                                    </ul>
                            
                                                                </nav>
                            
                                                            </div>
                            
                                                        </div>
                            
                                                        <% } %>
                            
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                            
                            
                                </div>
                            </div>

            </div>




           
        </div>
    </section>

    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>